---
import hands from "../assets/safe-hands.webp";
import community from "../assets/community.webp";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
---

<section class="about-section" aria-label="About Lupus Together" id="about">
  <div class="section-wrapper">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2 class="section-title">About Lupus Together</h2>
      <p id="about-subtitle" class="about-subtitle">
        You're not alone. We're in this together
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-content content">
      <div class="text-image-row">
        <Image
          src={hands}
          alt="Supportive hands symbolizing care and connection"
          class="float-image img-one"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <p>
          Lupus Together is a safe and welcoming space for people living with
          lupus, their families, and their friends. Whether you are newly
          diagnosed, living with lupus for years, or caring for someone who is,
          this is where connection begins.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="text-image-row reverse-row">
        <Image
          src={community}
          alt="Group of friends providing support"
          class="float-image img-two"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <p>
          We started in 2012 in Cape Town South Africa. A small group of friends
          came together, each with someone close to them affected by lupus. What
          began as a few honest conversations quickly grew into something more.
          A place where people could be seen, heard, and supported without
          judgment.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="mission-statement">
        Lupus Together was created so no one has to face this condition in
        silence.
      </p>

      <h3 class="about-subheading">What you'll find in our community</h3>

      <ul class="about-list" aria-label="Lupus Together Community Services">
        <li>
          <span role="img" aria-label="Flower Icon">üåº</span>
          Circle Chats - weekly check-ins guided by lived experience
        </li>
        <li>
          <span role="img" aria-label="Handshake Icon">ü§ù</span>
          Buddy Bench - match with someone who understands
        </li>
        <li>
          <span role="img" aria-label="Books Icon">üìö</span>
          Lupus Library - helpful stories and bite-sized support guides
        </li>
        <li>
          <span role="img" aria-label="Microphone Icon">üéôÔ∏è</span>
          Lupus Talks - real conversations from people walking this path
        </li>
        <li>
          <span role="img" aria-label="Speech Bubble Icon">üí¨</span>
          Private Forum - a safe space to share, ask, and connect
        </li>
      </ul>

      <blockquote class="about-quote" aria-label="Community Testimonial Quote">
        <Icon
          name="quote"
          size={24}
          style={{
            marginRight: "8px",
            color: "var(--primary-color)",
          }}
        />
        For once, I did not have to explain everything. They just understood
        <span class="community-author">- Community Member</span>
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  #about-subtitle {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .about-subheading {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .about-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding-left: 0;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .about-list li {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.125rem);
  }

  .about-list li span {
    margin-right: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1.25em;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .about-quote {
    background-color: var(--quote-background-color);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--primary-color);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
    padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-color);
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.125rem);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .community-author {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--secondary-color);
  }
</style>
